===Etymology===
: Slavic ''voda'', ''woda'', meaning [[water]], plus the diminutive suffix ''-ka''. Historical documentary research of V. Pokhlyobkin suggests the derivation via the usage "dilution (of [[distil]]late) with water", as used in expressions "vodka of grain wine" and similar; ''grain wine'' ([[хлебное вино]]) is an archaic Russian name for vodka.

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# A clear [[distil]]led [[alcoholic]] [[liquor]] made from [[grain]] [[mash]].
# A serving of the above beverage.

